UNITED STATES of America, Appellee, v. George DE ANGELO, Defendant-Appellant. No. 8127. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Submitted on Briefs Nov. 18, 1942. Decided Dec. 7, 1942. Anthony A. Calandra, of Newark, N. J., for appellant. Richard J. Hughes and Charles M. Phillips, both of Trenton, N. J., for appellee.

Before BIGGS, MARIS, and GOODRICH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the court below is affirmed.
